Reasoning: The paper discusses mechanisms for achieving atomic commitment of distributed transactions in the context of a Web services atomic transaction framework. This involves coordination among multiple replicas and fault tolerance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.Distributed Systems.
